HEADWORD: Potentiality
<hw>Po*ten`ti*al"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality
or state of being potential; possibility, not actuality; inherent
capability or disposition, not actually exhibited.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Potentially</ent>⟦br⟧
